        • Get all champion mastery entries sorted by number of champion points descending,
        Jump to Inputs

        Response Classes

        Return value: List[ChampionMasteryDTO]

        ChampionMasteryDTO
        - This object contains single Champion Mastery information for player and champion combination.
        Name Data Type Description
        chestGranted boolean Is chest granted for this champion or not in current season.
        championLevel int Champion level for specified player and champion combination.
        championPoints int Total number of champion points for this player and champion combination - they are used to determine championLevel.
        championId long Champion ID for this entry.
        playerId long Player ID for this entry.
        championPointsUntilNextLevel long Number of points needed to achieve next level. Zero if player reached maximum champion level for this champion.
        championPointsSinceLastLevel long Number of points earned since current level has been achieved. Zero if player reached maximum champion level for this champion.
        lastPlayTime long Last time this champion was played by this player - in Unix milliseconds time format.

        Response Errors

        - This object contains champion information.
        Name Data Type Description
        rankedPlayEnabled boolean Ranked play enabled flag.
        botMmEnabled boolean Bot Match Made enabled flag (for Co-op vs. AI games).
        botEnabled boolean Bot enabled flag (for custom games).
        active boolean Indicates if the champion is active.
        freeToPlay boolean Indicates if the champion is free to play. Free to play champions are rotated periodically.
        id long Champion ID. For static information correlating to champion IDs, please refer to the LoL Static Data API.

        503 Service unavailable
        504 Gateway timeout

        Path Parameters

        Name Value Data Type Description

        Query Parameters

        optional

    current-game-v1.0

    • Collapse Operations
    • Expand Operations
      • GET /observer-mode/rest/consumer/getSpectatorGameInfo/{platformId}/{summonerId}
        • Get current game information for the given summoner ID. (REST)
        Jump to Inputs

        Response Classes

        Return value: CurrentGameInfo

        CurrentGameInfo

        Name Data Type Description
        gameId long The ID of the game
        gameStartTime long The game start time represented in epoch milliseconds
        platformId string The ID of the platform on which the game is being played
        gameMode string The game mode
        mapId long The ID of the map
        gameType string The game type
        bannedChampions List[BannedChampion] Banned champion information
        observers Observer The observer information
        participants List[CurrentGameParticipant] The participant information
        gameLength long The amount of time in seconds that has passed since the game started
        gameQueueConfigId long The queue type (queue types are documented on the Game Constants page)
        BannedChampion

        Name Data Type Description
        pickTurn int The turn during which the champion was banned
        championId long The ID of the banned champion
        teamId long The ID of the team that banned the champion
        Observer

        Name Data Type Description
        encryptionKey string Key used to decrypt the spectator grid game data for playback
        CurrentGameParticipant

        Name Data Type Description
        profileIconId long The ID of the profile icon used by this participant
        championId long The ID of the champion played by this participant
        summonerName string The summoner name of this participant
        runes List[Rune] The runes used by this participant
        bot boolean Flag indicating whether or not this participant is a bot
        masteries List[Mastery] The masteries used by this participant
        spell2Id long The ID of the second summoner spell used by this participant
        teamId long The team ID of this participant, indicating the participant's team
        spell1Id long The ID of the first summoner spell used by this participant
        summonerId long The summoner ID of this participant
        Rune

        Name Data Type Description
        count int The count of this rune used by the participant
        runeId long The ID of the rune
        Mastery

        Name Data Type Description
        masteryId long The ID of the mastery
        rank int The number of points put into this mastery by the user

        Response Errors

        HTTP Status Code Reason
        429 Rate limit exceeded
        403 Forbidden

        Path Parameters

        Name Value Data Type Description
        summonerId
        required
        		long The ID of the summoner.

    • Collapse Operations
    • Expand Operations
      • GET /api/lol/{region}/v1.3/game/by-summoner/{summonerId}/recent
        • Get recent games by summoner ID. (REST)
        Jump to Inputs

        Response Classes

        Return value: RecentGamesDto

        RecentGamesDto
        - This object contains recent games information.
        Name Data Type Description
        games Set[GameDto] Collection of recent games played (max 10).
        summonerId long Summoner ID.
        GameDto
        - This object contains game information.
        Name Data Type Description
        gameType string Game type. (Legal values: CUSTOM_GAME, MATCHED_GAME, TUTORIAL_GAME)
        gameId long Game ID.
        stats RawStatsDto Statistics associated with the game for this summoner.
        level int Level.
        createDate long Date that end game data was recorded, specified as epoch milliseconds.
        gameMode string Game mode. (Legal values: CLASSIC, ODIN, ARAM, TUTORIAL, ONEFORALL, ASCENSION, FIRSTBLOOD, KINGPORO, SIEGE)
        mapId int Map ID.
        invalid boolean Invalid flag.
        subType string Game sub-type. (Legal values: NONE, NORMAL, BOT, RANKED_SOLO_5x5, RANKED_PREMADE_3x3, RANKED_PREMADE_5x5, ODIN_UNRANKED, RANKED_TEAM_3x3, RANKED_TEAM_5x5, NORMAL_3x3, BOT_3x3, CAP_5x5, ARAM_UNRANKED_5x5, ONEFORALL_5x5, FIRSTBLOOD_1x1, FIRSTBLOOD_2x2, SR_6x6, URF, URF_BOT, NIGHTMARE_BOT, ASCENSION, HEXAKILL, KING_PORO, COUNTER_PICK, BILGEWATER, SIEGE, RANKED_FLEX_SR, RANKED_FLEX_TT)
        teamId int Team ID associated with game. Team ID 100 is blue team. Team ID 200 is purple team.
        ipEarned int IP Earned.
        fellowPlayers List[PlayerDto] Other players associated with the game.
        championId int Champion ID associated with game.
        spell1 int ID of first summoner spell.
        spell2 int ID of second summoner spell.

      • GET /lol/match/v3/matchlists/by-account/{accountId}
        • Get matchlist for ranked games played on given account ID and platform ID and filtered using given filter parameters, if any.
        Jump to Inputs

        Implementation Notes

        A number of optional parameters are provided for filtering. It is up to the caller to ensure that the combination of filter parameters provided is valid for the requested account, otherwise, no matches may be returned. Note that if either beginIndex or endIndex are specified, then both must be specified and endIndex must be greater than beginIndex. If endTime is specified, but not beginTime, then beginTime is effectively the start of the account's match history. If beginTime is specified, but not endTime, then endTime is effectively the current time. Note that endTime should be greater than beginTime if both are specified, although there is no maximum limit on their range.

    matchlist-v2.2

    • Collapse Operations
    • Expand Operations
      • GET /api/lol/{region}/v2.2/matchlist/by-summoner/{summonerId}
        • Retrieve match list by summoner ID. (REST)
        Jump to Inputs

        Implementation Notes

        A number of optional parameters are provided for filtering. It is up to the caller to ensure that the combination of filter parameters provided is valid for the requested summoner, otherwise, no matches may be returned. If either of the beginTime or endTime parameters is set, they must both be set, although there is no maximum limit on their range. If the beginTime parameter is specified on its own, endTime is assumed to be the current time. If the endTime parameter is specified on its own, beginTime is assumed to be the start of the summoner's match history.

        role string (Legal values: DUO, NONE, SOLO, DUO_CARRY, DUO_SUPPORT)
        season string (Legal values: PRESEASON3, SEASON3, PRESEASON2014, SEASON2014, PRESEASON2015, SEASON2015, PRESEASON2016, SEASON2016, PRESEASON2017, SEASON2017)
